"Supporting our talent in basketball will not only mould us into superstars, but will act as an avenue where girls are so much engaged to never engage in early pregnancies, drugs and alcohol abuse besides other immoral behaviors,” she explained. 






Kakuma Bulls Girls Basketball team pose for a photograph before a training session at Kakuma Refugee Camp in Turkana County on December 17, 2020.
Photo credit: Jared Nyataya | Nation Media Group

 

The girls called on the Kenya Basketball Federation to also visit them and offer necessary support in terms of training facilities. 

Lolem Welpan, 22, said that when playing basketball on the court it is difficult to differentiate them basing on the nationalities. 

Promoting peace 

She said that there are South Sudanese, Kenyans, Somalis, Burundians, Congolese and Rwandese. 



