"The sport is promoting peace among us and is the best avenue to appreciate each other's culture." She said. 

According to senior youth development officer at the Lutheran World Federation, Tom Aduwa, the youth in Kakuma are positive. 

“Despite many challenges at the camp, youths in Kakuma are very proactive, hardworking and talented. 

“They do not shy from taking up opportunities that come their way and their networking skills are also high. 

“With proper support and networking, especially with the national sports bodies, Kakuma youth will surprise the country, and the world,” said Aduwa. Education CS George Magoha says government will provide three million needy learners with masks. In most schools, lack of classrooms, desks, water, toilets, and dormitories is a stark reality. A new twist in the battle between DP Ruto and his political foe Gideon Moi, for control of vote-rich Rift Valley.